WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.440
Canterbury Tales. Jeffrey Chaucer. Teen Ailey Readers. Copyright Ailey 2014.

00:12.320 --> 00:15.120
Chapter 1 The Prologue

00:17.440 --> 00:23.200
It's a beautiful day. The weather is good, the birds are singing,

00:23.200 --> 00:30.320
the grass is green and there are flowers everywhere. Now my story can begin.

00:32.080 --> 00:38.800
My name's Jeffrey and today I'm going on a pilgrimage to Canterbury.

00:40.000 --> 00:45.280
I'm going to Canterbury with a group of people. We're going there together.

00:45.520 --> 00:50.960
I met these people yesterday at an inn in London.

00:53.360 --> 00:59.920
I arrived at the inn in the afternoon. I was very tired and hungry.

01:01.280 --> 01:07.520
Good afternoon, I said to the man who worked at the inn, he was the innkeeper.

01:08.480 --> 01:13.200
I'd like a room for the night. I'm going to Canterbury tomorrow.

01:13.920 --> 01:19.040
The road to Canterbury is long. I need to sleep well before I start.

01:20.720 --> 01:26.480
Good afternoon, said the innkeeper. Do you know that some other people are going to

01:26.480 --> 01:34.560
Canterbury tomorrow? They're staying here tonight. I'd like to meet them, I said to the innkeeper.

01:34.800 --> 01:45.200
In the evening, I met the other people. The inn was big and there was a lot of good food and drink.

01:45.200 --> 01:52.720
Everybody had dinner together and the innkeeper gave good food to everybody.

01:52.720 --> 02:01.360
The innkeeper was a nice person. He was a very big man and he enjoyed speaking to people.

02:02.320 --> 02:08.000
He was very good at his job. Everybody enjoyed their dinner.

02:10.320 --> 02:14.000
After dinner, the innkeeper spoke to the group.

02:15.760 --> 02:23.200
You're a very nice group of people, he said. I know that God will listen to your prayers.

02:24.240 --> 02:30.640
You're all going to the same place. So you must go to Canterbury together.

02:30.720 --> 02:31.680
What do you think?

02:33.040 --> 02:36.480
Yes, we can go together, I said.

02:37.600 --> 02:41.840
And I want to go to Canterbury with you, said the innkeeper.

02:43.040 --> 02:51.680
Now, we have to travel for a long time. And I think we can do something interesting.

02:52.800 --> 02:55.920
We can play a game. What do you think?

02:56.720 --> 03:02.240
Yes, said everybody in the group. Tell us about this game.

03:03.360 --> 03:08.080
Now, listen to what I have to say, said the innkeeper.

03:09.280 --> 03:15.680
We'll go to Canterbury together and every person will tell a story.

03:17.120 --> 03:24.000
I'll listen to every story, then I'll tell you which story is the best.

03:26.080 --> 03:29.200
Everybody in the group wanted to play this game.

03:30.880 --> 03:38.800
Very well, said the innkeeper, and I will give something to the person who tells the best story.

03:40.240 --> 03:45.680
That person will have dinner at my inn and I'll pay for the dinner.

03:47.840 --> 03:54.800
The people in the group were very happy and they began to think of what story to tell.

03:56.640 --> 04:05.520
In the group, there was a night. Everybody liked him, and he was always happy to help people.

04:07.120 --> 04:15.920
He was an important man, but his clothes were cheap. His horse was fast, but it was small.

04:16.560 --> 04:22.400
I'm a knight, and my life is very exciting, said the knight.

04:23.440 --> 04:33.120
And my story is also going to be exciting. It's about two brothers who love the same woman.

04:35.840 --> 04:43.040
There was also a clerk in the group. He was a nice man, but he didn't speak very much.

04:43.200 --> 04:49.360
He liked reading and studying. That's all he wanted to do.

04:50.960 --> 04:58.640
He was very slim, and he didn't eat very much, and he liked books more than food.

05:01.520 --> 05:04.720
I read a lot of books, said the clerk.

05:04.720 --> 05:12.320
I don't want nice clothes or good food. I don't have much money.

05:13.760 --> 05:20.880
And I use the money I have to buy books. That's why I read a lot of stories.

05:22.880 --> 05:32.080
My story is very easy to understand, but it's not boring. I think everybody will enjoy it.

05:32.960 --> 05:36.880
It's about a king who has many secrets.

05:39.680 --> 05:45.840
Another person in the group was a merchant. He had a lot of money,

05:46.880 --> 05:52.400
but he wasn't a happy man. He always had a sad face.

05:54.320 --> 06:00.080
He was different from the night. His clothes were very expensive.

06:00.800 --> 06:06.400
Everything he had was expensive, his clothes, his hat, and his horse.

06:08.960 --> 06:12.400
I have an important business, said the merchant.

06:13.440 --> 06:19.600
And I have a lot of things to do, but I'm not very happy with my life.

06:21.200 --> 06:28.880
And that's why my story will be sad. It'll be about an old man who can't see.

06:30.080 --> 06:37.200
I also have to tell you about another man. He was a Franklin.

06:38.320 --> 06:45.360
He was different from the clerk. He was very rich and important, but he didn't have a business.

06:46.640 --> 06:55.200
He had a big house in the country, and he often invited people there. He liked good food.

06:55.200 --> 07:00.960
I'm very old, and my house is big.

07:02.000 --> 07:05.920
And I like inviting people there, said the Franklin.

07:07.360 --> 07:16.080
In my house, I often tell stories. I enjoy it. My story will be very interesting.

07:17.200 --> 07:23.840
It's about a woman who doesn't like to see. Why doesn't she like to see?

07:25.360 --> 07:28.480
Well, you'll have to listen to my story.

07:31.200 --> 07:39.280
There is another person I want to tell you about. He was a gardener. He also liked reading.

07:40.480 --> 07:46.880
And he liked to sing songs and say prayers. He had a strange face.

07:47.680 --> 07:54.320
I travel a lot, and I always say prayers for people, said the gardener.

07:55.280 --> 08:05.520
There are a lot of bad people in the world. I'll say a prayer for them, but they have to give me some money.

08:06.320 --> 08:12.960
My story will be about three people who do something very bad.

08:12.960 --> 08:21.040
Everybody was tired. It was late in the evening, and the night said,

08:22.160 --> 08:26.880
we can go to bed now. Then we can leave early in the morning.

08:28.400 --> 08:33.440
We all went to bed. We were tired, but happy.

08:36.080 --> 08:42.560
Early next morning, we got up, and then we left for Canterbury on our horses.

08:43.920 --> 08:53.120
We were slow. And after many hours, we came to a place called St. Thomas, and we stopped there.

08:54.640 --> 09:02.720
We sat down, and then we had something to eat. After eating, the innkeeper said,

09:03.680 --> 09:07.280
listen, do you remember what we said last night?

09:08.720 --> 09:10.720
Of course, said the night.

09:12.080 --> 09:19.920
Well, said the innkeeper, who wants to begin? Who wants to tell the first story?

09:21.600 --> 09:30.080
I'm happy to tell you my story, said the night. I think you will enjoy it. It's very exciting.

09:30.080 --> 09:35.120
And then the night began to tell his story.

09:38.960 --> 09:42.240
Chapter 2 The Night's Tale

09:45.040 --> 09:54.160
My story is about two brothers, said the night. Their names were Palamon and Arcyte, and they were

09:54.160 --> 10:01.920
knights. The brothers were from a city called Thebes. They did everything together.

10:02.800 --> 10:09.360
They weren't only brothers. They were also friends. But they were very sad.

10:11.200 --> 10:17.120
They were sad because they didn't live in Thebes anymore. They lived in Athens.

10:18.240 --> 10:22.640
And they didn't live in a house. They lived in a prison.

10:24.320 --> 10:28.720
They couldn't leave the prison, and they couldn't speak to anybody.

10:30.160 --> 10:38.800
Every morning, they looked out of the prison window. From their window, they could see a beautiful

10:38.800 --> 10:50.720
garden. One morning, Palamon woke up, and then he looked out of the window. But something was

10:50.720 --> 11:00.480
different. There was a woman in the garden. Her name was Emily. She was the daughter of the

11:00.480 --> 11:01.680
king of Athens.

11:03.920 --> 11:16.160
Look, said Palamon. That woman is beautiful. Oh, I'm in love. Arcyte, come here. Look.

11:16.720 --> 11:29.040
Arcyte went to the window, and he saw the woman. Yes, you're right. She is beautiful, he said.

11:30.000 --> 11:42.160
One day, I'll marry her. I saw her first, said Palamon. You can't love her. You must help me.

11:42.720 --> 11:52.000
No, said Arcyte. My love is perfect. You must help me.

11:54.400 --> 12:02.080
Arcyte and Palamon both loved Emily, and they had the same conversation every day.

12:03.440 --> 12:11.680
I love her. No, you can't love her was all you could hear from the small room, their prison.

12:13.120 --> 12:21.920
And then, one day, a friend of Arcyte's visited the king of Athens. He wanted to speak to the

12:21.920 --> 12:33.280
king about Arcyte. Can he go home? Asked Arcyte's friend. He's a good man, and I want to see him again.

12:34.160 --> 12:44.800
I'll do what you ask, said the king. Arcyte can go home, but he must never come to Athens again,

12:44.800 --> 12:57.440
and Palamon must stay in prison. Arcyte went back to Thebes, but he wasn't happy. I'm going home,

12:58.080 --> 13:07.920
thought Arcyte, but I can't see Emily. Palamon can see her in the garden. It's better in prison.

13:10.160 --> 13:20.880
But Palamon was sad as well. Arcyte, you can go back to Athens, he thought. You can fight the

13:20.880 --> 13:27.440
king of Athens, and you can marry Emily. I have to stay in this prison.

13:30.160 --> 13:36.720
In Thebes, Arcyte was very sad. He didn't sleep or eat very much.

13:38.480 --> 13:44.880
I'll wait for two years, thought Arcyte, and then I'll go to Athens again.

13:45.840 --> 13:54.480
Nobody will know me. I'll wear different clothes. I'll change my name, and I'll find a job.

13:55.440 --> 14:02.000
I'll be a servant in the king's house. And then I'll see Emily.

14:04.320 --> 14:13.440
And that's why, after two years, Arcyte went back to Athens, and soon he was the king's servant.

14:15.360 --> 14:18.960
The king liked Arcyte because he was good at his job.

14:20.560 --> 14:27.760
One day, Arcyte went to a forest near Athens, and he sat near a tree.

14:29.360 --> 14:39.840
What can I do, said Arcyte? I'm the king's servant. I'm near Emily, but she doesn't know who I am.

14:40.720 --> 14:42.480
I want to die.

14:45.120 --> 14:50.800
Then a man spoke to Arcyte. It was Palamon.

14:52.800 --> 14:59.760
Hello, brother. It's me, said Palamon. Stop thinking about Emily.

15:00.800 --> 15:02.800
Only I can love her.

15:02.880 --> 15:09.920
Palamon, it's you, said Arcyte. Why aren't you in prison?

15:11.280 --> 15:19.120
The king sent me home yesterday. But I'm not going home. I want to find Emily.

15:20.640 --> 15:30.240
Well, I'll fight you for Emily, said Arcyte. But not today. We're knights, remember? We must do

15:30.240 --> 15:39.040
things in the right way. Tonight, I'll bring some food. And then tomorrow, we'll fight.

15:40.640 --> 15:45.680
All right, said Palamon. And so the brothers said goodbye.

15:47.360 --> 15:53.760
On the next day, they met in the forest. And then they started fighting.

15:54.400 --> 16:05.760
On the same day, the king was also in the forest. He was with Emily, and he saw Palamon and Arcyte.

16:06.640 --> 16:12.640
Stop, said the king. What are you doing? Stop now.

16:12.640 --> 16:13.360
Stop now.

16:15.360 --> 16:23.360
Kill us, said Arcyte. Now I'm your servant. And before that, I was in your prison.

16:24.720 --> 16:35.200
My name is Arcyte. And this is my brother, Palamon. We're fighting because we both love Emily.

16:36.080 --> 16:44.320
Then you must die, said the king. But Emily stopped as the king.

16:45.840 --> 16:51.040
Please don't kill them, she said. They're fighting for love.

16:53.280 --> 17:01.440
Well, said the king. You're right, Emily. But only one of them can marry you.

17:02.400 --> 17:10.000
Palamon, Arcyte, come back to the forest next summer. Bring a hundred knights.

17:11.040 --> 17:15.840
And then you'll fight for Emily. Now go.

17:18.560 --> 17:27.520
Soon it was summer. Palamon and Arcyte came back to Athens. They both had a hundred knights,

17:27.600 --> 17:30.320
and they were ready to fight the next day.

17:32.800 --> 17:39.120
That night, Palamon had a dream. In his dream, a woman said,

17:40.080 --> 17:44.800
I can see you. You are marrying Emily.

17:46.880 --> 17:53.680
On the same night, Arcyte also had a dream. In his dream, a man said,

17:54.640 --> 18:02.320
I can hear you. You are saying, hooray. Emily will be my wife.

18:04.800 --> 18:10.320
Which dream was right? Well, now I'll tell you.

18:12.720 --> 18:20.560
In the morning, everybody came to the forest. The knights were ready, and they began to fight.

18:20.960 --> 18:28.640
After three hours, Emily was worried. They're fighting for me.

18:29.840 --> 18:33.760
Who's going to be my husband? When will they stop?

18:35.520 --> 18:42.880
And then after many hours, they did stop. Palamon was very tired.

18:43.840 --> 18:48.480
Stop, he said. I can't fight anymore.

18:50.000 --> 18:55.840
Stop fighting, said the king. Arcyte will be Emily's husband.

18:57.200 --> 19:07.600
Hooray, said Arcyte. I'm very happy. Emily will be my wife. I must go to her and…

19:07.840 --> 19:15.600
But then, Arcyte stopped speaking. He didn't feel very well.

19:18.160 --> 19:26.240
People came to help Arcyte. I'm not well, said Arcyte. I can't…

19:27.600 --> 19:34.640
I can't feel anything. I'm dying. This is the end.

19:35.520 --> 19:42.720
Goodbye, Emily, my love. Goodbye, Palamon, my brother.

19:45.040 --> 19:56.160
And then, Arcyte died. Soon, it was winter, and the king called for Palamon and Emily.

19:56.320 --> 20:04.960
As you know, Arcyte died last summer, and it was very sad, said the king.

20:04.960 --> 20:16.400
Emily, I want you to be happy. Palamon, you must marry Emily. It's the right thing to do.

20:17.120 --> 20:29.680
Thank you, said Palamon. Arcyte was a good night. He was my dear brother. But, we had to fight for love.

20:30.800 --> 20:42.240
Emily, I know we'll be happy together, but we'll never forget my brother. He died for love.

20:46.880 --> 20:50.640
Chapter 3 The Clark's Tale

20:52.960 --> 20:56.080
The Clark was the next person to tell his story.

20:57.600 --> 21:03.760
I have an interesting story, he said. It's about a king called Walter.

21:04.880 --> 21:11.360
He was the king of Saluche in Italy. Walter wanted to marry a woman,

21:12.240 --> 21:17.760
but only he knew the name of this woman. It was his secret.

21:19.360 --> 21:26.560
The woman's name was Griselda. She was young and beautiful, and she was very nice.

21:28.000 --> 21:32.800
She was very poor, and she lived in a small house with her father.

21:33.760 --> 21:36.640
She cooked and cleaned for him every day.

21:37.920 --> 21:43.120
And now, I'll tell you their story, said the Clark.

21:46.960 --> 21:50.960
One day Griselda was at home with her father.

21:52.720 --> 22:00.000
Today is the day, said Griselda. Today we'll know the name of the king's wife.

22:00.640 --> 22:04.800
Who will it be? It's very exciting.

22:06.960 --> 22:11.920
I think his wife will be a rich woman, said Griselda's father.

22:13.360 --> 22:20.000
But Griselda's father was wrong, and soon he heard somebody at the door.

22:21.120 --> 22:28.400
Griselda's father opened the door, and he saw Walter, the king of Saluche.

22:30.160 --> 22:36.640
I want to speak to you. I want to marry Griselda, said Walter.

22:37.920 --> 22:43.920
Griselda, my Griselda, said the father.

22:45.440 --> 22:54.320
But this is strange. We're poor, and you're the king. Why do you want a poor wife?

22:55.200 --> 23:01.280
That's not important, said Walter. She's the woman I love.

23:02.720 --> 23:04.160
Can I speak to her?

23:05.760 --> 23:09.200
Well, of course, said the father.

23:11.280 --> 23:16.960
And then Walter went inside the house, and he spoke to Griselda.

23:17.760 --> 23:25.840
Griselda, said Walter. Will you be my wife? You must do everything I say.

23:27.840 --> 23:38.800
I'm too poor for you, said Griselda. I cook and clean. I work hard. I have a different kind of life.

23:39.760 --> 23:49.120
But I want you to be happy. I'll be your wife, and I promise to do everything you say.

23:50.960 --> 23:53.520
That's good, said Walter.

23:55.120 --> 24:04.000
And then Griselda went home with Walter. Servants arrived. They gave Griselda a beautiful dress,

24:04.640 --> 24:08.960
and on that day, Walter married Griselda.

24:11.440 --> 24:17.280
Walter and Griselda were very happy. The people of the city liked her.

24:18.640 --> 24:28.640
Soon, Griselda had a beautiful baby girl. Walter was also happy, but he was worried about something.

24:28.880 --> 24:41.120
Griselda is very nice, he thought. But does she love me? Is she only nice because I'm the king?

24:42.640 --> 24:45.360
I have to know that she loves me.

24:47.520 --> 24:51.200
Then, Walter did something very bad.

24:52.000 --> 25:01.360
One night, Griselda was in her room. She was with her daughter. Walter's servant came into the room.

25:02.400 --> 25:11.600
I'm sorry it's late, said the servant, but I must do what the king says. I must take your daughter.

25:12.800 --> 25:18.800
The servant took the child from Griselda. Griselda was very worried.

25:19.440 --> 25:26.880
What's he going to do with my daughter? Is he going to kill her? Thought Griselda.

25:28.320 --> 25:30.240
But Griselda said nothing.

25:32.000 --> 25:38.400
Now go, said Griselda to the servant, and do what the king says.

25:40.960 --> 25:44.000
Then the servant took the child to Walter.

25:44.960 --> 25:49.600
Don't tell anybody about this, said Walter to his servant.

25:51.280 --> 25:59.760
Go with my daughter to Milan. She'll live with my sister. But remember, it's a secret.

26:00.720 --> 26:04.000
Nobody must know that this girl is my daughter.

26:05.840 --> 26:09.360
And then the king's servant took the child to Milan.

26:09.360 --> 26:16.320
What did Griselda do? Did she hate her husband?

26:18.000 --> 26:24.240
The answer to this question is no. Griselda didn't change.

26:26.320 --> 26:34.080
Does Griselda love me or not? thought the king. Oh, I don't know.

26:34.400 --> 26:47.280
After five years, Griselda had another baby. It was a boy. Griselda was happy again.

26:49.200 --> 26:58.000
But Walter wasn't happy. Griselda, said Walter, do you promise that you'll always love me?

26:58.960 --> 27:07.200
Yes, I do, said Griselda. I'm your wife, and I left my old life.

27:08.160 --> 27:15.120
I left my house and my father. I'll die for you. Is that what you want?

27:16.960 --> 27:24.000
But Walter wasn't happy. I have to know that she loves me, he thought.

27:24.800 --> 27:36.160
Soon, Griselda's son was two years old. One night, Griselda was in her room. She was with her son.

27:37.360 --> 27:40.560
Then the servant came into her room again.

27:40.880 --> 27:47.600
I must take your son, he said. It's what the king wants.

27:50.000 --> 27:55.120
First my daughter and now my son thought Griselda.

27:56.720 --> 28:01.840
Oh, my children, what will Walter do to my son?

28:02.400 --> 28:06.560
Griselda said goodbye to her son.

28:07.840 --> 28:10.960
And then the servant took the child to Walter.

28:12.720 --> 28:16.320
Take my son to Bologna, said Walter.

28:17.600 --> 28:20.800
And remember, this must be a secret.

28:22.720 --> 28:28.560
And then the servant left. He took the boy to a family in Bologna.

28:28.560 --> 28:36.960
Now I'll know, thought the king. Will Griselda love me now?

28:39.200 --> 28:45.120
But Griselda didn't change. She didn't hate Walter, she was good to him.

28:46.880 --> 28:53.760
I don't know what Walter is thinking, thought Griselda. I promised to love him,

28:54.560 --> 29:00.000
and I will love him. But why does he do these bad things?

29:02.880 --> 29:12.080
For some years, Walter was happy. His daughter was in Milan, and she was now 18 years old.

29:13.280 --> 29:21.520
And Walter began to worry again. Does Griselda love me? He thought again.

29:21.680 --> 29:25.600
And then he did another bad thing.

29:27.280 --> 29:30.720
The king called for Griselda, and he said to her,

29:32.160 --> 29:42.080
I don't need you anymore. I want a new wife. Griselda said nothing, and then she left Walter's room.

29:44.880 --> 29:50.960
Walter then spoke to his servant. Bring me my son and daughter, he said.

29:51.680 --> 29:56.720
But it must be a secret. Don't tell anybody who these children are.

29:57.680 --> 30:03.520
I'll say to everybody that I'm going to marry the girl. Of course, I'm not going to marry her.

30:03.520 --> 30:06.880
She's my daughter. But nobody will know this.

30:09.520 --> 30:13.440
That afternoon, Walter spoke to Griselda again.

30:13.440 --> 30:24.960
Griselda, a poor woman can't be my wife. I was wrong, he said. My new wife is arriving.

30:25.920 --> 30:32.880
You must go back to your father's home. Leave your clothes here. I'll give them to my new wife.

30:33.440 --> 30:47.680
Thank you for everything, said Griselda. I'll go home to my father. He's old. I want you to be happy with your new wife.

30:49.280 --> 30:51.120
And then she left the room.

30:53.680 --> 31:02.160
The king was very sad. I hate doing this, he thought. I love her so much.

31:03.040 --> 31:06.080
But I must know that she loves me.

31:08.400 --> 31:15.920
The next day, Walter went to Griselda's house. He wanted to ask Griselda something.

31:17.440 --> 31:26.640
Griselda, as you know, my new wife is arriving, said Walter. I need somebody to clean her room.

31:27.600 --> 31:28.720
Will you help me?

31:29.600 --> 31:33.440
I'll be happy to help, said Griselda.

31:35.040 --> 31:43.040
And then she went to Walter's house. She cleaned the rooms, she made the beds, and she washed the plates.

31:45.120 --> 31:49.120
That morning, Griselda's son and daughter arrived.

31:50.640 --> 31:58.400
When Griselda saw the girl, she thought, she's beautiful. And she thought of her daughter.

31:59.360 --> 32:02.640
My daughter is the same age, she thought.

32:04.080 --> 32:07.760
And when Griselda saw the boy, she thought of her son.

32:09.280 --> 32:14.640
The boy is so clever. My son is the same age.

32:16.080 --> 32:19.920
Of course, she didn't know that they were her children.

32:21.600 --> 32:24.400
When Griselda saw the king, she said,

32:25.360 --> 32:33.840
that girl is very nice. She's beautiful. Be nice to her. I hope you'll be happy.

32:35.520 --> 32:40.800
Stop this, said the king. I don't want to do this anymore.

32:41.920 --> 32:52.640
My dear wife Griselda, I love you very much. Griselda, you are my wife, and you're perfect.

32:53.600 --> 32:57.840
And then, Walter called for his son and daughter.

32:59.360 --> 33:08.000
Griselda, this is our daughter, and not my new wife, and this is our son.

33:09.520 --> 33:17.280
I'm very sorry. I only wanted you to love me, and now I know that you do.

33:18.640 --> 33:21.040
These are our children.

33:23.600 --> 33:26.800
Griselda was happy to see her children again.

33:28.160 --> 33:33.760
Thank you, thank you, said Griselda. My children are safe.

33:35.840 --> 33:43.200
That night they had a big party. Griselda and Walter were both very happy.

33:44.480 --> 33:48.960
And Walter never worried about Griselda's love again.

33:49.040 --> 33:55.920
Chapter 4 The Merchants' Tale

33:58.160 --> 34:00.320
The merchant told the next story.

34:01.680 --> 34:08.720
I travel a lot, he said. And everywhere I go, I see people that are sad.

34:10.080 --> 34:16.880
I have a wife. But do you think I'm happy? Well, I'm not happy.

34:17.840 --> 34:22.560
My wife isn't a nice person, and I hate my life.

34:24.000 --> 34:31.520
I want to tell you a story about a husband and wife. It's a story about a rich, old man.

34:32.640 --> 34:41.040
His name is January. January wanted to find a wife, and he asked his friends to help him.

34:41.120 --> 34:47.600
Don't find me an old wife, said January. I want a young wife.

34:48.800 --> 34:53.840
January's friends found a wife for him. Her name was May.

34:54.400 --> 34:58.080
She was young, but she didn't have any money.

34:59.840 --> 35:07.840
January was happy with his wife. I'm old, he thought. But now I've got a young wife.

35:08.480 --> 35:14.640
I won't have any more problems. And May is very beautiful.

35:17.120 --> 35:21.040
But there was another person who thought that May was beautiful.

35:22.320 --> 35:31.040
It was January's servant. His name was Damien. Damien thought of May all the time.

35:32.080 --> 35:37.440
He didn't sleep very much. He didn't want to eat. He loved May.

35:38.720 --> 35:43.360
And now he had to see her every day with January.

35:45.040 --> 35:51.840
Soon Damien wasn't well. He didn't want to go to work anymore, and he stayed in bed.

35:53.040 --> 35:59.920
In bed, he wrote a letter to May. Then he put the letter in a small bag.

36:00.240 --> 36:08.080
That evening, January went to dinner. Where's my servant Damien? He said.

36:09.520 --> 36:14.560
Damien isn't well, said another servant. He's in bed now.

36:16.160 --> 36:25.360
I'm sorry about that, said January. He's a good servant. He works hard. I want to speak to him.

36:25.840 --> 36:31.120
After dinner, May and January visited Damien.

36:32.320 --> 36:36.720
May went to see Damien first. She sat next to him.

36:38.320 --> 36:40.320
How are you? Asked May.

36:42.080 --> 36:50.480
Damien didn't say anything. He took the letter out of his bag, and then he gave the letter to May.

36:50.640 --> 36:55.760
Don't speak to anybody about this letter, he said.

36:57.920 --> 37:04.560
When May was at home, she read Damien's letter. It was a love letter.

37:06.000 --> 37:12.400
May didn't know what to do. Damien doesn't know my secret, she thought.

37:12.400 --> 37:19.360
I love Damien, but he is poor, and my husband is rich.

37:20.800 --> 37:26.880
How can I help Damien? I want him to be well again, thought May.

37:28.560 --> 37:33.760
May wrote a letter to Damien, and then she visited him again.

37:33.760 --> 37:37.120
She gave Damien the letter.

37:38.560 --> 37:43.680
Get well soon Damien, she said, and then she left.

37:45.920 --> 37:53.280
Damien read the letter. The letter changed him. Soon he was well again.

37:54.480 --> 38:02.720
The next morning Damien got up. Now he was happy. Now he wanted to go to work.

38:04.720 --> 38:11.600
January had a big house, and he had a beautiful garden. He often went there.

38:12.880 --> 38:19.280
It was his favorite place. Only January and May could go to the garden.

38:20.480 --> 38:25.920
January had a key, and he used the key to go into the garden.

38:26.160 --> 38:34.160
One day January was in his garden. He looked at the trees and the flowers.

38:35.200 --> 38:42.480
It was a beautiful day. The weather was perfect, but January didn't feel very well.

38:43.680 --> 38:52.240
Help, help, said January. I can't see. I can't see anything. I'm blind.

38:52.320 --> 38:58.960
It was very sad. January couldn't see any more.

39:00.560 --> 39:05.040
May went to the garden, and she took January back to the house.

39:06.800 --> 39:14.400
January stayed in his room for two months. He didn't want to go out, and he often thought about May.

39:15.040 --> 39:22.000
What about May? He thought. Now I can't see my beautiful wife.

39:23.200 --> 39:27.280
What is she doing? I can't see what she's doing.

39:28.640 --> 39:37.600
Does she love me? I know what I'll do. I'll tell her that she must always stay in the house.

39:38.320 --> 39:40.320
We'll stay here together.

39:40.880 --> 39:50.480
The next day, January said to May, you must always sit next to me. Then I'll know what you're doing.

39:50.480 --> 39:56.240
Sometimes we can go to the garden, but we must go there together.

39:57.680 --> 40:07.680
Now it was May who was sad. Her house was a prison, and she thought more and more about Damien.

40:08.000 --> 40:11.600
Damien was also sad.

40:12.880 --> 40:18.160
I can't speak to May, he thought. January is always there.

40:18.880 --> 40:26.960
I must do something. I need to speak to May. May and Damien often wrote letters to each other.

40:27.920 --> 40:34.960
They wrote about their love. But Damien wanted more. He wanted to speak to May.

40:35.760 --> 40:47.520
He wrote a letter to her. In the letter he wrote, May, take a key to the garden, and then give the key to me.

40:48.800 --> 40:57.280
January has a lot of keys. Then tell January that you want to go to the garden. Do it now.

40:57.600 --> 41:06.000
Damien gave the letter to May, and May did what Damien asked. She gave him the key.

41:07.680 --> 41:13.200
Then Damien went to the garden, and he waited there for January and May.

41:15.440 --> 41:21.360
Soon January and May were in the garden. January was happy again.

41:22.160 --> 41:32.320
I'm old, and I can't see, he said to May. But I have you, my love. I love you so much.

41:33.200 --> 41:40.720
And I want to show you how much I love you. Tomorrow I'm going to give you all my money,

41:40.720 --> 41:43.120
and this house, and this garden.

41:44.000 --> 41:51.360
January, what are you saying, said May? You're the only man in my life.

41:52.640 --> 41:58.800
But of course, there was another man in May's life, and that man was Damien.

42:00.000 --> 42:03.280
And now she saw Damien in the garden.

42:03.840 --> 42:13.840
I'm hungry, said May. I want to go to the apple tree. Then I can eat an apple. Wait here.

42:15.200 --> 42:22.560
But May didn't want any apples. She didn't go to the tree. She ran to meet Damien.

42:23.360 --> 42:34.800
January waited for May. He didn't know where she was. Now, she was with Damien. But then,

42:35.600 --> 42:37.120
everything changed.

42:39.120 --> 42:48.480
I can see again. I can see, said January to himself. How is this possible? He thought.

42:49.280 --> 42:56.080
January didn't understand. I must tell May. She'll be so happy.

42:57.280 --> 43:02.800
And so, January looked at the apple tree. But May wasn't there.

43:04.160 --> 43:12.960
Where's May? Thought January. And then he saw her. But he didn't only see May.

43:13.840 --> 43:16.080
He also saw a man.

43:17.680 --> 43:20.240
Who are you? What are you doing?

43:21.360 --> 43:24.880
Leave this garden now, said January.

43:26.480 --> 43:29.280
Damien and May looked at January.

43:31.040 --> 43:36.640
I think he can see us, said Damien. And then Damien ran.

43:37.840 --> 43:41.840
He was very fast, and soon he was outside the garden.

43:43.600 --> 43:46.480
Then May ran to speak to January.

43:48.000 --> 43:50.560
What is it, my love? She asked.

43:52.480 --> 43:57.680
I can see now. I was so happy. I wanted to tell you.

43:58.880 --> 44:04.640
And then I saw you with a man. I think I saw you with somebody.

44:05.520 --> 44:16.720
You can see again, said May. I'm so happy. But what are you talking about? A man?

44:17.600 --> 44:25.680
You can look everywhere in this garden. But you won't see a man. Because there is no man.

44:26.960 --> 44:31.840
I was so excited that I could see again, said January.

44:32.640 --> 44:39.360
I think I saw something that wasn't there. But I thought there was somebody with you.

44:40.800 --> 44:46.080
There was no man, said May. Nobody can come into the garden.

44:47.360 --> 44:53.360
I want to go back home, my love. Then you can sleep. You're tired.

44:54.720 --> 44:58.000
Yes. You're right, said January.

44:58.800 --> 45:04.800
Of course, there wasn't a man. Nobody can come into the garden.

45:06.240 --> 45:12.320
I want to go home now. We have to tell everybody, we'll have a party.

45:12.880 --> 45:18.800
Isn't it great? I'm not blind. I can see again.

45:19.680 --> 45:29.280
And here my story ends, said the merchant. January was happy. He could see again.

45:30.640 --> 45:37.600
But there was something that January couldn't see. He couldn't see that May didn't love him.

45:38.480 --> 45:44.960
And that May loved Damien. January wasn't blind anymore.

45:45.760 --> 45:49.600
But love is always blind.

45:53.280 --> 45:57.040
Chapter 5 The Franklin's Tale

45:59.680 --> 46:09.200
Everybody in the group was tired. It was the end of a long day. They were ready to listen to the Franklin story.

46:09.760 --> 46:18.320
My story is also about her husband and wife. But this story is different from the merchant story.

46:19.360 --> 46:30.000
In my story, love is not blind. The husband and wife in my story are in love. The wife's name was

46:30.960 --> 46:38.720
Dorigen. She loved her husband very much. The husband's name was Arviragos.

46:39.920 --> 46:48.640
He was a knight. They lived in France. But when I start my story, Arviragos was in England.

46:49.520 --> 46:57.760
Dorigen was very sad. She thought about her husband every day. And she stayed at home.

47:00.800 --> 47:09.120
Arviragos wrote a letter to Dorigen. Don't worry. I'll come home soon, he wrote.

47:10.640 --> 47:18.240
Dorigen read the letter. I don't want him to come back soon. I want him to come back now, she thought.

47:19.280 --> 47:23.440
But I must go out. I must try to be happy.

47:24.400 --> 47:35.040
And so, Dorigen started going out. Her house was near the sea. She often went for a walk there with her friends.

47:35.040 --> 47:45.440
And she always wanted to look at the sea. Where is the boat, thought Dorigen, that will bring me my husband?

47:46.240 --> 47:55.920
And sometimes, she looked at the big black rocks in the sea. I don't like the sea, said Dorigen to her friends.

47:55.920 --> 48:10.720
Look at those black rocks. They're dangerous. Dorigen's friends were very worried. You must stop thinking about those dangerous black rocks, they said.

48:11.680 --> 48:19.200
And so, Dorigen's friends took her to a dance. But she didn't want to dance.

48:20.720 --> 48:30.240
At the dance, there was a man called Aurelius. He loved Dorigen. And he wanted to speak to her.

48:30.240 --> 48:44.640
Dorigen, you don't know me very well. My name is Aurelius. You're so beautiful. Is there a place in your heart for me?

48:44.640 --> 48:53.840
Dorigen looked at Aurelius and said, no, there isn't. I'll always love my husband.

48:54.640 --> 49:10.240
But what will I do? I need you, said Aurelius. I'm sorry, said Dorigen. But, said Aurelius, is there anything I can do?

49:10.240 --> 49:23.040
Hmm, well, I want the black rocks in the sea to disappear. Do this and then there will be a place in my heart for you.

49:23.840 --> 49:28.560
But that's not possible, said Aurelius. Nobody can do this.

49:29.840 --> 49:38.320
I know, said Dorigen. Aurelius went home. At home, he said a prayer.

49:39.440 --> 49:52.160
Help me, he said. And then he went to bed. And he stayed at home. He never went out. He didn't want to see anybody.

49:53.840 --> 50:03.840
Soon, Dorigen's husband came home. Dorigen and Arviregas were together again. Aurelius was at home.

50:03.840 --> 50:16.480
He was always at home. One day, Aurelius read an interesting book. It was a book about magic.

50:16.480 --> 50:25.280
I can use magic. With magic, the black rocks will disappear, thought Aurelius.

50:25.280 --> 50:36.160
I know a man in Orlio. His name is Simon. He's famous for his magic. I can ask him to help me.

50:36.160 --> 50:41.440
The next day Aurelius went to Simon's house.

50:41.440 --> 50:48.640
Hello, said Simon. Have dinner with me and you can tell me everything.

50:48.640 --> 51:02.720
At dinner there was every kind of food. There was meat, fish, fruit and vegetables. They ate and Aurelius told Simon his story.

51:03.680 --> 51:09.120
Simon listened to the story. And then he said,

51:09.120 --> 51:16.480
It's true that I sometimes do magic. And now I'll do some magic for you.

51:18.000 --> 51:21.920
And then the food on the table disappeared.

51:24.000 --> 51:31.360
Aurelius was very happy. Can you help me, said Aurelius, with the black rocks?

51:33.120 --> 51:41.040
Yes, I can, said Simon. But it'll be expensive. You have to pay me a thousand pounds.

51:42.560 --> 51:51.280
That's a lot of money, said Aurelius. But all right, you must be quick. I want to go home tomorrow.

51:53.360 --> 52:02.000
In the morning they went back to Aurelius' house. Simon started work and after two days he was ready.

52:03.200 --> 52:10.000
Aurelius, he said, We can go and see the black rocks. They went to the sea.

52:11.200 --> 52:15.840
But when they arrived, the black rocks weren't there anymore.

52:17.360 --> 52:24.160
Oh, thank you. Thank you so much, said Aurelius. I must show this to Dorogen.

52:24.160 --> 52:29.360
The next day Aurelius met Dorogen.

52:30.880 --> 52:37.760
Hello, Dorogen, he said. Do you remember our conversation about the dangerous black rocks?

52:38.560 --> 52:43.840
Do you remember what you promised? Please tell me that you remember.

52:45.200 --> 52:51.760
Yes, I remember, said Dorogen. Well, said Aurelius,

52:52.480 --> 52:55.680
the black rocks aren't there anymore. Come and see.

52:57.680 --> 53:08.160
When they arrived, Dorogen looked at the sea. And then she said, But how can black rocks disappear?

53:09.280 --> 53:16.800
What can I do? I have to speak to my husband. And then she ran back home.

53:17.280 --> 53:27.280
When Dorogen arrived home, she started to think. I made a promise. And promises are important.

53:28.000 --> 53:32.960
But I'll never do anything bad to my husband. What can I do?

53:34.160 --> 53:42.640
For two days, Dorogen thought about her problem. What can I say to my husband, she thought.

53:43.120 --> 53:50.320
Then Dorogen spoke to her husband. She told him everything.

53:52.000 --> 54:00.800
Don't worry, said Arveragus. You did nothing wrong. But you promised this to Aurelius.

54:01.920 --> 54:08.960
And that's why you must leave me. But I love you, Arveragus, said Dorogen.

54:09.920 --> 54:11.680
Oh, what can I do?

54:13.520 --> 54:21.760
Dorogen went to a garden. She needed to think. When she was in the garden, a man spoke to her.

54:23.680 --> 54:28.960
Hello. Where are you going? It was Aurelius.

54:29.120 --> 54:39.200
I don't know, said Dorogen. My husband says I must leave him. The black rocks aren't there anymore.

54:39.760 --> 54:45.120
And I promise to be with you. Dorogen was very sad.

54:46.880 --> 54:54.320
Dorogen stopped speaking. And then something changed inside Aurelius' heart.

54:55.120 --> 55:05.120
I hate to see you this sad, he said. Your husband is a good man. You and Arveragus have a perfect love.

55:06.000 --> 55:12.960
I must stop this. Go home to your husband. We'll forget about your promise.

55:14.640 --> 55:21.440
Thank you, Aurelius. Thank you. Oh, I'm so happy, said Dorogen.

55:22.400 --> 55:25.360
And then she went home to tell her husband.

55:27.680 --> 55:34.880
Then Aurelius remembered something. I have to pay Simon a thousand pounds.

55:35.680 --> 55:44.080
And I only have five hundred pounds. What am I going to do? I'll bring him five hundred pounds.

55:44.880 --> 55:46.480
I think he'll understand.

55:47.360 --> 55:57.600
Aurelius went back to Simon's house. Aurelius was very worried. Simon won't be very happy, he thought.

55:58.640 --> 56:02.880
Hello, said Simon. Do you have my money?

56:03.840 --> 56:08.080
I can give you five hundred pounds, said Aurelius.

56:09.280 --> 56:14.560
Why don't you pay me everything? I did everything you asked of me, didn't I?

56:14.640 --> 56:18.080
The black rocks disappeared?

56:19.360 --> 56:24.960
Yes, they did, said Aurelius. And I'm very sorry about the money.

56:26.400 --> 56:33.680
And then Aurelius told Simon everything. He told him about Dorogen and Arveragus.

56:34.400 --> 56:37.280
He told him about their perfect love.

56:37.600 --> 56:47.200
Your all very good people, said the man. You did a very good thing. You have a good heart.

56:48.240 --> 56:53.440
And I want to be good as well. You forgot about Dorogen's promise.

56:54.240 --> 57:00.320
And so I'll forget about the thousand pounds. I won't take any money from you.

57:00.320 --> 57:08.160
Thank you, Simon, said Aurelius. And then Aurelius went home.

57:09.760 --> 57:17.920
I'll never be with Dorogen, he thought. But I'm happy, because I did a good thing.

57:19.520 --> 57:26.800
And that is the end of my story, said the Franklin. As you can see,

57:27.520 --> 57:35.680
it's different from the merchant story, because this story tells us that there are also many

57:35.680 --> 57:37.520
good people in the world.

57:40.960 --> 57:44.880
Chapter 6 The Pardiner's Tale

57:46.880 --> 57:52.720
And now I have a story for you, said the partner to the other people in the group.

57:53.600 --> 58:01.360
It's a story about three men. They were called Amis, Lucian and Maurice.

58:03.040 --> 58:11.040
Amis talked a lot. The other two men didn't talk very much. These men were very bad.

58:11.920 --> 58:18.560
They only thought about money. They were always together, but they weren't friends.

58:19.440 --> 58:29.760
Friends help you. Friends listen to your problems. They were greedy, and they had no love in their hearts.

58:31.360 --> 58:39.200
I will begin my story in an inn. The three men were together at a table near the window.

58:39.200 --> 58:45.040
I'm hungry, said Amis.

58:46.400 --> 58:54.640
So am I, said Lucian. I want something to eat. But then Amis saw something strange.

58:55.520 --> 59:01.040
Look, he said. Look out of the window. What are those two men doing?

59:01.840 --> 59:07.360
Oh yes, said Lucian. They're carrying a man.

59:08.800 --> 59:14.160
You're right, said Amis. Who is he? I think we know him.

59:15.040 --> 59:17.040
Yes, it's Adranos.

59:18.240 --> 59:22.400
Inkeeper, said Amis. Is that Adranos?

59:23.920 --> 59:30.240
Yes, it is. Adranos died last night. Somebody killed him.

59:30.880 --> 59:32.000
Said the innkeeper.

59:33.600 --> 59:36.960
Who did this to Adranos? Asked Amis.

59:38.080 --> 59:40.960
Death did it, said the innkeeper.

59:42.400 --> 59:48.880
Death? That's a strange name, said Amis. Why is he called Death?

59:50.240 --> 59:53.920
Because of the things he does, said the innkeeper.

59:54.720 --> 01:00:02.000
Last week he met five people, and he killed them all. Nobody can find him.

01:00:03.040 --> 01:00:05.280
Everybody is worried about Death.

01:00:07.040 --> 01:00:17.760
We'll look for him, said Amis. It'll be good fun. We'll find him, and we'll fight this strange man called Death.

01:00:18.560 --> 01:00:24.160
Don't do it, said the innkeeper. He's very dangerous.

01:00:25.360 --> 01:00:29.280
Don't worry. We know what to do, said Amis.

01:00:31.200 --> 01:00:36.160
People say that Death lives near the mountain, said the innkeeper.

01:00:36.800 --> 01:00:42.160
Don't go near the mountain, or you'll be the next people to die.

01:00:42.160 --> 01:00:48.560
Why? Well, we're going to the mountain. Nothing will stop us.

01:00:50.080 --> 01:00:56.560
And so the three men left the inn, and then they started walking to the mountain.

01:00:58.480 --> 01:01:03.280
The three men walked for a long time. They often had to stop.

01:01:04.640 --> 01:01:08.560
After some hours, the three men met an old man.

01:01:09.360 --> 01:01:12.560
Hey, old man, said Amis.

01:01:13.600 --> 01:01:16.160
What do you want, said the old man?

01:01:17.440 --> 01:01:19.600
Do you know a man called Death?

01:01:21.040 --> 01:01:27.520
Yes, I know about him, said the old man. But why are you asking me this?

01:01:28.400 --> 01:01:31.920
Don't go near that man. He's dangerous.

01:01:32.800 --> 01:01:36.000
Tell us where we can find him, said Amis.

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:41.040
Nobody knows where he is, said the old man.

01:01:42.320 --> 01:01:49.040
But people say he often goes to a place. They say he puts his money there.

01:01:50.480 --> 01:01:54.560
Money, said Amis. Where is this place?

01:01:56.400 --> 01:02:00.640
Before you walk up the mountain, there's a very old tree.

01:02:01.920 --> 01:02:07.600
It's near the road that goes to the mountain. Sometimes he goes there.

01:02:08.640 --> 01:02:11.280
They say he's got a lot of money.

01:02:12.640 --> 01:02:18.880
I think I know where this tree is, said Amis. We can go there now.

01:02:20.080 --> 01:02:29.280
No, stop, said the old man. But it was too late. The friends wanted to find the tree.

01:02:31.920 --> 01:02:38.400
After two hours, they arrived at the place, and they saw the tree.

01:02:40.320 --> 01:02:45.120
I want to look for the money now, said Amis. Do you remember?

01:02:45.760 --> 01:02:48.400
The old man said that Death put it here.

01:02:50.160 --> 01:02:56.640
They looked for the money, and soon they found it. It was under a small rock.

01:02:57.440 --> 01:03:04.560
There was a lot of money in a big bag. The bag was very difficult to carry.

01:03:06.320 --> 01:03:11.760
Here it is. Look how much there is. We're rich, said Amis.

01:03:12.800 --> 01:03:19.600
Hooray, they said. We've got a lot of money. They were very excited.

01:03:21.280 --> 01:03:24.560
I want to get something to eat and drink, said Amis.

01:03:25.520 --> 01:03:30.720
Okay, said Lucian. We can go to the town and buy something.

01:03:32.160 --> 01:03:37.440
But wait, said Amis. Two of us must wait here with the money.

01:03:38.320 --> 01:03:42.640
Maurice, you go to the town. We'll wait for you here.

01:03:44.480 --> 01:03:48.560
Okay, said Maurice, and he went to the town.

01:03:50.080 --> 01:03:52.960
The other two men waited under the tree.

01:03:54.720 --> 01:03:57.920
After an hour, Amis thought of something.

01:03:59.360 --> 01:04:04.000
Listen, said Amis. There's a lot of money in that bag.

01:04:05.680 --> 01:04:13.920
Yes, you're right, said Lucian. There's about 600 pounds. That's 200 pounds each.

01:04:15.440 --> 01:04:20.640
Yes, but I think we can have 300 pounds each.

01:04:20.720 --> 01:04:23.840
How, said Lucian?

01:04:25.120 --> 01:04:31.440
Well, we can kill Maurice when he comes back. Then we'll have more money.

01:04:32.800 --> 01:04:41.040
Yes, I want to do that, said Lucian. And then the two men waited for Maurice.

01:04:42.720 --> 01:04:47.760
Maurice was near the town and he started thinking.

01:04:48.640 --> 01:04:57.360
Well, there's about 600 pounds in that bag. That's about 200 pounds for me.

01:04:58.800 --> 01:05:05.680
200 pounds is a lot of money. But 600 pounds is much more.

01:05:06.480 --> 01:05:15.440
600 pounds will change my life. I know what I'll do. I'll kill Amis and Lucian.

01:05:16.080 --> 01:05:18.320
Then I'll have all the money.

01:05:20.560 --> 01:05:27.280
Ten minutes later, Maurice arrived at the town. He bought some food and drink.

01:05:28.400 --> 01:05:37.040
But he also bought some poison. He put the poison in the drink and then he went back to the tree.

01:05:37.680 --> 01:05:55.680
It was getting late when Maurice arrived. Amis, Lucian, I've got the food and they were the last words that Maurice spoke because then Amis and Lucian killed him.

01:05:55.920 --> 01:06:04.960
And now we have more money, said Amis. They didn't worry about Maurice.

01:06:07.120 --> 01:06:15.120
The two men were happy. They drank together. Soon the poison was in their bodies.

01:06:16.480 --> 01:06:20.320
And after one minute, the poison killed them.

01:06:20.720 --> 01:06:25.600
That's the end of my story, said the partner.

01:06:26.800 --> 01:06:35.040
The three men wanted to fight death. They were greedy. And that's why they died.

01:06:36.480 --> 01:06:44.160
I want you to remember this story when we arrive at Canterbury and when we say our prayers.

01:06:44.560 --> 01:06:48.880
The others thought it was a very good story.

01:06:50.080 --> 01:06:53.680
And then the people in the group thought about all the stories.

01:06:54.960 --> 01:07:04.320
There were a lot of things to think about. And after four days, Canterbury was very, very near.

